This is a missed-optimization in InstCombine.

The following program reveals the missed optimization.
The source program is
```llvm
define i8 @xor_shl(i8 %x, i8 %y, i8 %zarg, i8 %shamt) {
  %z = sdiv i8 42, %zarg
  %sx = shl i8 %x, %shamt
  %sy = shl i8 %y, %shamt
  %a = xor i8 %z, %sx
  %r = xor i8 %a, %sy
  ret i8 %r
}

```

However, current LLVM cannot optimize the source program. The expected optimized program is
```llvm
define i8 @xor_shl(i8 %x, i8 %y, i8 %zarg, i8 %shamt) {
  %z = sdiv i8 42, %zarg
  %1 = xor i8 %x, %y
  %2 = shl i8 %1, %shamt
  %r = xor i8 %2, %z
  ret i8 %r
}

```
Please modify the following code in llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp:InstCombinerImpl::foldBinOpShiftWithShift to implement the missed optimization:
```cpp
